addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-00KR</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>To see that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[g\colon  B\to  A]]></fr:tex> is unique, we fix any other <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[g']]></fr:tex> that is simultaneously a <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00KS.xml"
addr="jms-00KS"
title="Section-retraction pair">retraction</fr:link> and a <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00KS.xml"
addr="jms-00KS"
title="Section-retraction pair">section</fr:link> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> and show that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[g=g']]></fr:tex>:</fr:p>
 <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[   \begin {aligned}     g &= \mathsf {id}_{A}\circ  g\\     &= {\mathopen {}\left (g'\circ  f\right )\mathclose {}} \circ  g\\     &= g'\circ {\mathopen {}\left (f\circ  g\right )\mathclose {}}\\     &= g'\circ \mathsf {id}_{B}\\     &= g'   \end {aligned}  ]]></fr:tex>
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
